cs.CE, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an extension of phase change and latent heat models for the simulation of metal powder bed fusion additive manufacturing processes on the macroscale, which involves computational engineering and science.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses different numerical schemes for the treatment of latent heat and proposes a novel variant of the heat integration scheme.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper compares different numerical schemes with respect to accuracy and numerical efficiency.
- cs.SI (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper proposes a systematic formulation of phase fraction variables relying on temperature- or enthalpy-based interpolation schemes, which can be seen as a control problem.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a less likely category but still possible as the paper proposes a new numerical scheme and compares it with existing ones, which can be seen as a software engineering problem.
